---
import LoanProductLayout from "@/layouts/LoanProductLayout.astro";
const title = "Invoice Discounting";
const subtitle = "Invoice discounting unlocks cash from unpaid invoices while you keep customer control. It's fast, confidential finance to smooth cash flow and fund growth.";
---
<LoanProductLayout title={title} subtitle={subtitle} updatedAt="November 2025">
  
  <!-- What is invoice discounting -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">What is invoice discounting?</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Invoice discounting is a short-term finance option that allows businesses to unlock a percentage of an invoice's value - usually between 70% and 90% - soon after it's raised. Once your client pays the invoice, the remaining balance is released to you, minus a fee.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
      It's a confidential facility, meaning your customers won't know you're using external finance. You stay in charge of chasing and collecting payments, maintaining full control over your customer relationships.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">How invoice discounting works</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">1</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Raise invoice</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You raise an invoice with your client.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">2</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Submit to lender</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You submit the invoice to your lender.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">3</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Receive advance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">The lender advances you a percentage of the invoice value.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">4</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Client pays</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Your client pays you as normal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">5</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Repay lender</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You repay the lender and keep the remaining balance, minus fees.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">Invoice discounting example</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
        Let's say you raise a €10,000 invoice. Your invoice discounting facility offers an 80% advance.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold">•</span>
          <span>Advance received: <strong>€8,000</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold">•</span>
          <span>Client pays full invoice: <strong>€10,000</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold">•</span>
          <span>Lender fee: <strong>€200</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold">•</span>
          <span>Final amount retained: <strong>€9,800</strong></span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4">
        You maintain control of the customer relationship while improving cash flow.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What can I use invoice discounting for -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">What can I use invoice discounting for?</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Support cash flow</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Cash tied up in unpaid invoices can become a burden on healthy cash flow. This is particularly true for B2B businesses, where 30, 60, and even 90 day terms are fairly standard. Invoice discounting can essentially remove this issue by providing the funds shortly after the invoice is raised.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Enable growth</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Growth often needs money to fuel it. Whether that's hiring new talent, promoting with more vigour across social media and paid ads, or purchasing new stock. Invoice discounting can be a way to provide some of that growth-enabling cash up front.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Cover emergencies</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">When a company emergency hits, for example, an essential piece of equipment breaks, getting the cash together can be tricky. Invoice discounting provides a suitable middle ground between taking out a long-term loan and paying the funds upfront.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Marketing</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Ads, agencies, content, and branding all cost money. The funds from invoice discounting could be used to lay the foundations for a solid marketing campaign, commit to a rebranding, onboard a new marketing intern, or increase ads distribution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Business development</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Whether you need to pay your new account executive or need to fund a trip abroad to close a deal, invoice discounting could be a suitable way to fund business development activities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Pay off a tax bill</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Sometimes, one or two months is all that's needed to cover a corporation tax or VAT bill. If you've found yourself in a similar circumstance, invoice discounting could be the answer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Costs and fees -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">Costs and fees: what affects pricing?</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Several factors can impact how much you'll be charged for invoice discounting:
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Invoice value and volume</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Higher, consistent volumes can attract better rates. The value of individual invoices also plays a role in risk assessment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Creditworthiness</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Strong credit histories generally mean lower costs. Lenders assess both business and personal credit scores.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Business size and track record</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">More established firms often get access to better terms. A longer trading history demonstrates reliability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Lender's risk perception</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Reliability of your clients and repayment history plays a part. Lenders assess the creditworthiness of your customers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Agreement type</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Confidential vs disclosed discounting can influence fees. Confidential arrangements may have different pricing structures.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Number of invoices</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Some lenders offer scalable pricing that reduces the fee per invoice as volume increases, making it more cost-effective for businesses with many invoices.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Pros and cons -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Pros and cons of invoice discounting</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">Pros</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Flexible and fast access to working capital</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Confidential arrangement - customers don't know</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Retain customer relationship control</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Scalable as business grows</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Often lower fees than invoice factoring</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">Cons</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-neutral-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-neutral-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">You're still responsible for chasing payments</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-neutral-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-neutral-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Not ideal for new or very small businesses</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-neutral-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-neutral-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Fees reduce overall invoice value</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-neutral-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-neutral-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Can lead to dependency if not managed carefully</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-neutral-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
              <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-neutral-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
            </div>
            <span class="text-neutral-700">Requires good credit control processes</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Is it right for your business -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Is invoice discounting right for your business?</h2>
    
    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">It may be a suitable option if your business:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Operates in a B2B environment</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Has invoices with 30–90 day terms</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Needs flexible working capital support</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Has a consistent track record of issuing and collecting invoices</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Has an annual turnover of €250,000 or more</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Startups and sole traders may benefit more from a short-term business loan or a government-backed startup loan. Invoice discounting is typically better suited to established businesses with proven credit control processes and consistent invoice volumes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Invoice discounting vs invoice factoring -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Invoice discounting vs invoice factoring</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200">
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Invoice Discounting</th>
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Invoice Factoring</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Client notified</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">No</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Who chases payment</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">You</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">The lender</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Confidentiality</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">High</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Lower</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Cost</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Often lower</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Typically higher</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Suitable for</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Established businesses</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Businesses needing support</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50 mt-6">
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-black">Key difference:</strong> Invoice discounting is similar to factoring, however there is one fundamental difference. With factoring, your customers might know that you're in receipt of finance because the lender will typically manage your sales ledger and credit control processes. As such, they'll chase any late payments on your behalf. On the other hand, invoice discounting allows you to retain autonomy over all communications and customer service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Alternatives -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Invoice discounting alternatives</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Invoice factoring</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Unlike invoice discounting, invoice factoring is the actual sale of your invoices in exchange for cash. The lender manages your sales ledger and chases payments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Bridging loans</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">A form of short-term funding, usually used to pay for property development or acquisitions while waiting for additional funding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Company credit card</h3>
